      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARMATREE ASAFA (7) settled down midfield and held his position to the line when finishing 4th (30.61) at this track. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Should be very hard to beat this time. ROY LEARY (1) was prominent early from the tricky draw and stalked the lead before levelling up to score (24.85) at this track in a Grade 5 over 431m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Leading chance again. GENERAL LEE (2) goes very well here starting nine times for three wins and three minors. Was out of placings last time (30.37) at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5, finishing fifth and beaten 7 lengths. Suited here and expected to run well. SCOOTIN' SCOOBY (6) has strong credentials from this draw.",
